{"_id":"pUPwqamnt9K4hSMQ","name":"Ghoul","permission":{"default":0,"hsFJxrWN4M5Ezw3L":3},"type":"race","data":{"associates":["Carnivorous Bite","Shadow Heritage","Tenacity","Ghoulish Determination","Low-Light Vision"],"skillbonuses":["Endurance","Stealth"],"speed":6,"description":"<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Average Height: 5&rsquo;2&rdquo;-6&rsquo;4&rdquo;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Average Weight: 130-210 lb.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Ability Scores: +2 Constitution, +2 Dexterity or Wisdom</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Speed: 6 squares</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Vision: Low-light</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Languages: Two mundane</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Skill Bonuses: +2 Endurance, +2 Stealth</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Carnivorous Bite: You may make bite attacks using your sharp teeth. Your bite attack is an alternate unarmed attack with a +2 precision bonus and a 1d8 damage die.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Shadow Heritage: You have both the natural and shadow creature origins. You may choose which origin applies at any time.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Tenacity: Whenever you succeed on a survival roll, you may regain &lt;CON&gt; hit points (minimum 1). If you do not choose to regain hit points, you instead stabilize.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Power: Ghoulish Determination: You have the <em>ghoulish determination</em> racial feature power, allowing you to occasionally ignore damage that would incapacitate you.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Physical Qualities</span></u></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Ghouls are thought to be humans altered by exposure to the shadowy power of the Underworld. They superficially resemble humans, but have several key differences which can be used to identify them. The most easily spotted is their teeth, which resemble the teeth of a shark, adapted for eating meat. Ghouls also have limbs which are longer and wirier than humans, which makes them look subtly misshapen, and they tend to be pallid and dark-haired.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: .25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Ghouls mature at the same rate as humans. Although they can live on more or less the same diet as humans, ghouls are obligate carnivores: they must have at least some meat in their diet, or suffer from malnutrition. However, a healthy ghoul is extremely difficult to kill: ghouls can recover from almost any injury as long as they have time and a supply of meat; in extreme cases, ghouls can regenerate in the middle of a fight using the flesh torn from their enemies.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Magical Qualities</span></u></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Ghouls are somehow connected to the Underworld, and traces of it linger in their bloodlines, giving them a tenuous link to the Underworld. This bond makes ghouls incredibly resilient; experienced ghoul hunters always apply a coup de grace to ensure that a downed ghoul remains down.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Culture and Attitudes</span></u></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">It is believed that ghouls are an artificially created race; they were first encountered just over a hundred years ago, and the first ghouls were found scavenging from graveyards and battlefields in an isolated region to the far south. At the time, most scholars suggested that ghouls were the product of experiments by a single isolated wizard, and were set free or left to fend for themselves. Later, when ghouls were discovered living in the Underworld, a lively debate arose: to this day, it is unknown whether ghouls were created by a wizard and transplanted to the Underworld, arose naturally in the Underworld and were brought into the Material Plane, or somehow managed to arise independently in both worlds at once. The only entities that might know the true answer are some of the older residents of the Underworld.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: .25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Many ghouls are uncivilized, no better than feral animals, but possessed of a dangerous cunning. They are generally wary around armed, prepared individuals, but when driven by hunger or confronted with an easy target, ghouls are known to attack in packs and drag still-living victims away for later meals. For this reason, feral ghouls are treated like dangerous animals, and are hunted down at the earliest opportunity.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: .25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">However, when raised in civilization, ghouls are perfectly capable of overcoming their instincts. Infant ghouls are sometimes spared by hunters uncomfortable with the implications of killing something that looks generally human, and these ghouls and their descendants are now well-known, if not exactly common, in civilized society. Although no better or worse, on average, than humans or other civilized races, these &ldquo;civic&rdquo; ghouls remain tainted by their feral cousins in the eyes of many. As such, even civic ghouls are frequently forced into messy, bloody jobs in order to meet their specialized dietary requirements: they can commonly be found as hunters, butchers, and slaughterhouse workers. The worst-off sometimes stoop to working in mortuaries and graveyards, which contributes to ghouls&rsquo; unsavory reputation.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: .25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">A small minority of ghouls are somewhere between civilized and completely feral: whether they learned by watching and mimicking other races, or are the product of a half-successful attempt to raise them in civilization, these ghouls remain dangerously unstable. While they can sometimes eke out a living on the fringes of society, they more often wind up as murderers, serial killers, and brigands.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: .25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Ghouls have a range of attitudes towards their human cousins. Some attempt to integrate entirely into human or other societies, and others resent attempts to deny their differences from baseline humans.</span></p>"},"flags":[],"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"sOVJk0IEMhy4UFSI","name":"Gnome","permission":{"default":0,"hsFJxrWN4M5Ezw3L":3},"type":"race","data":{"associates":["Fey Heritage","Instinctive Stealth","Trickster's Intuition","Undersized","Fade Away"],"skillbonuses":["Arcana","Stealth"],"speed":5,"description":"<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Average Height: 4&rsquo;0&rdquo;-4&rsquo;10&rdquo;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Average Weight: 75-85 lb.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Ability Scores: +2 Intelligence and +2 Dexterity or Wisdom</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Speed: 5 squares</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Vision: Normal</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Languages: Two mundane</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Skill Bonuses: +2 Arcana, +2 Stealth</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Fey Heritage: You have both the natural and fey creature origins. You may choose which origin applies at any time.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><a name=\"_Hlk502156551\"></a><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Instinctive Stealth: You may make a Stealth check to hide when you roll initiative.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"mso-bookmark: _Hlk502156551;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Trickster&rsquo;s Intuition: You gain a +5 racial bonus to recovery rolls against illusion effects.</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Undersized: You gain a +1 size bonus to AC, Reflex, and attack rolls vs. AC and Reflex, a +2 size bonus to Stealth, and a -1 penalty to Fortitude.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Power: Fade Away: You have the&nbsp;<em>fade away&nbsp;</em>racial feature power, allowing you to briefly turn invisible to escape or set up an ambush.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Physical Qualities</span></u></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Gnomes are shorter than halflings, but stockier than goblins. Most gnomes have ruddy complexions and vibrant hair colors: chestnut brown, fiery red, or bright yellow. Their eyes are similarly vibrant: bright greens and piercing blues are common. Male gnomes can grow some facial hair (seldom more than a mustache and goatee), and both genders usually let their hair grow wild and spiky. Like elves, gnomes have pointed ears.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: .25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Gnomes grow at the same rate as humans, and are considered adult at the age of 18.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: .25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Magical Qualities</span></u></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">All gnomes have an innate ability to evade notice. If a gnome does not wish to be seen, watchers&rsquo; eyes will often pass them over without registering anything. With training, this ability can be honed into a form of invisibility.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Culture and Attitudes</span></u></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Most gnomes live in small, self-sufficient communities in Faerie, and are content to live out humble, peaceful lives. Gnomes fish, hunt, and live off the land rather than farm, and seldom attract attention to themselves&mdash;although anyone who finds a gnomish settlement and enters in peace can count on a warm welcome, full of laughter, music and merrymaking, since gnomes rarely receive visitors. Gnomes have an innate gift for illusion magic, and many of them use it to become unparalleled practical jokesters.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: .25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">However, since the Sidhe came to power, many gnomish communities have hidden themselves or moved into the deeper parts of Faerie, as they have learned to expect mistreatment from the Sidhe: when the Sidhe become aware of a gnomish community, they often conscript heavily from it in order to have gnomish spies and illusionists, or they demand tribute in the form of spellwork.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: .25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">The origin of gnomes is hotly debated in academic circles. Although it might simply be due to their tendency to hide, there is no record of gnomes existing, either on the Material Plane or in Faerie, prior to the Collapse. Various theories suggest that they are descendants of mortal races that crossed into Faerie and became trapped, similar to how the Sidhe were once elves, or how goblins became boggarts after generations trapped in the Underworld. Some of these theories suggest that gnomes are descended from halflings, due to a general physical resemblance. Other, less charitably, suggest that their fondness for hiding comes from goblin ancestry. A third theory, only recently gaining traction and still rejected by elven scholars, is that gnomes were intentionally created from elven stock by the Sidhe after their ascent to power, only to escape and go into hiding. Gnomes themselves have little to say on the subject.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: .25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Although most gnomes would prefer to hide from danger, many find themselves forced into action as the Sidhe tighten their control over Faerie. Few actively take up arms, but many gnomish enclaves provide shelter to resistance fighters, serving as safehouses and way-stations. Those gnomes who do join the fight are more likely to do so as saboteurs and spies, but there are a handful who put their invisibility and illusions to work as assassins. For fear of reprisals, most gnomes who join the resistance travel far from home before joining up, so that they cannot be connected back to their family and friends.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: .25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Other gnomes flee Faerie entirely, and make new lives in the material world. Gnomish communities have sprung up all over the world&mdash;although fewer than average around Caras Elvaren. While gnomes generally get along well with elves, given their matching affinities for magic and nature, the Sidhe possess more influence in Caras Elvaren than elsewhere, and the looming threat of Faerie agents inspires many gnomes to live further afield. Many gnomish communities are founded near halfling communities: aside from their similar size, gnomes appreciate the pastoral lifestyle of halflings that have settled down.</span></p>"},"flags":[],"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"w8NU27gsORfJ2rA2","name":"High Elf","permission":{"default":0,"hsFJxrWN4M5Ezw3L":3},"type":"race","data":{"associates":["Disciplined Mind","Extended Training","Elf Weapon Proficiencies","Deadly Grace"],"skillbonuses":["Arcana","History"],"speed":6,"description":"<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Average Height: 5&rsquo;4&rdquo;-6&rsquo;6&rdquo;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Average Weight: 125-190 lb.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Ability Scores: +2 Dexterity and +2 Intelligence or Wisdom</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Speed: 6 squares</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Vision: Normal</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Languages: Modern Elven, one other mundane</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.3333px; text-indent: 0px;\">Skill Bonuses: +2 Arcana, +2 History</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Disciplined Mind: You gain a +5 racial bonus to recovery rolls against charm effects and a +2 bonus to Insight checks made to resist magical influence.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Extended Training: You gain training in one extra skill from your class skill list.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Elven Weapon Proficiencies: Bows and Heavy Blades</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Power: Deadly Grace: You have the <em>Deadly Grace</em> racial feature power, allowing you to dodge an incoming attack and strike back.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Physical Qualities</span></u></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Elves are roughly as tall as humans, but have slender frames. Their hair has mostly the same range of colors as humans, although it tends to be more vibrant. High elves tend towards blonde or black hair, and wood elves are more commonly brown- or red-haired. A very few elves have hair of strange shades, like blue, green or purple, which is typically a sign of sorcerous ancestry. Both male and female elves let their hair grow long.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: .25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Elven children mature slightly slower than humans; they are considered mature (physically and mentally) on their 25<sup>th</sup> birthday. Due to this, elves tend to have a broader education by the time they go out into the world. Once mature, however, their aging slows considerably. Elves do not show signs of old age until they are at least 200 years old; many live to be 350 or older.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: .25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Culture and Attitudes</span></u></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">In the aftermath of the Collapse, the elven civilization splintered over their reactions to the catastrophe. The two largest factions came to be known as the High and Wood Elves.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: .25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">The High Elves wished to continue living much as they had previously. They renounced their former rulers, the Sidhe, who had led them to such ruin, but retained many aspects of the culture that the Sidhe has created: the high elves kept their focus on arcane magic, and when they began to rebuild, they modeled their new nation, Caras Elvaren, on the best parts of their fallen empire, Caras Sidharen. </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: .25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">High elves value learning and knowledge, especially in the arcane arts. Many high elves dabble in magic, even if their focus lies elsewhere. They also prize arts, music, and theater.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: .25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">High elven society is ruled by a council of Houses&mdash;essentially guilds which govern crucial services ranging from providing food and water, to healing the sick and protecting far-flung elven enclaves. Elves who are not part of these guilds are nominally represented by the guild of magisters, ascetic mages who have sworn service to the elven people&mdash;in practice, not all of the guildless are satisfied with this.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: .25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">In contrast to the high elves, the wood elves renounced the arcane as the ultimate cause of the Collapse, and withdrew into the deepest forests they could find. There, they lived as hunters and woodsmen. In the first century after the Collapse, this was a bleak existence: they could barely feed their people without using the arcane conveniences that had supported Caras Sidharen. Over time, the wood elves began to use primal magics, forming a bond with the nature spirits which inhabited their forests. These spirits created bountiful, hidden glades and led the elves to plentiful hunting grounds, which provided enough food to bring them back from the brink of starvation. Wood elves tend to learn practical skills due to their humble lifestyles, especially the arts of war; young wood elves are expected to train in archery or swordplay so that they can protect their villages and join in hunting parties. Wood elven art tends to be practical as well; woodcarving and weaving are common trades, although wood elves also have a rich history which is recited in verse by bards. </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: .25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">The wood elves have a reclusive society, nestled in the heart of a primeval forest. In theory, they are ruled by a queen who possesses absolute power, but in practice, the current queen is more interested in hunting and revelry. Actual governance is left to various local lords, as well as various sects of druids, and the way that laws are actually enforced varies widely between regions: some lords are noble and fair, some share the queen&rsquo;s preoccupation with hunting and revelry, and others are wildly xenophobic, preying on any outsider who wouldn&rsquo;t be missed.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: .25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">High elves tend to be soft-spoken, with impeccable manners. Wood elves are less reserved, at least when they are at home&mdash;but wood elves venturing into the wider world for the first time tend to be somewhat overwhelmed and introverted. Because of this, elves from both cultures have a reputation for aloofness or arrogance&mdash;which is accurate in some cases, but this isn&rsquo;t really the norm.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: .25in; tab-stops: right 3.75in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">There are other elven cultures&mdash;some elves have integrated into human societies, for example. There are also the feysworn elves, who serve the Sidhe in Faerie, and the dark elves, a loose collection of outcasts who seek to conquer or destroy humanity for their role in the Collapse and the destruction of Caras Sidharen. </span></p>"},"flags":[],"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"wwZ1dEf2Bth4MeWL","name":"Traditionist Dwarf","permission":{"default":0,"hsFJxrWN4M5Ezw3L":3},"type":"race","data":{"associates":["Dwarven Stoutness","Resilient Metabolism","Stout Stamina","Dwarven Dedication","Traditionist Dwarf Weapon Proficiencies","Low-Light Vision"],"skillbonuses":["Endurance","History"],"speed":5,"description":"<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in; text-indent: -0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Average Height: 4&rsquo;6&rdquo;-5&rsquo;4&rdquo;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in; text-indent: -0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Average Weight: 160-220 lb.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in; text-indent: -0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in; text-indent: -0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Ability Scores: +2 Constitution, +2 Strength or Wisdom</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in; text-indent: -0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Speed: 5 squares</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in; text-indent: -0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Vision: Low-light</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in; text-indent: -0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Languages: Low Dwarven, one other mundane</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in; text-indent: -0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Skill Bonuses: +2 Endurance, +2 History</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in; text-indent: -0.25in;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in; text-indent: -0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; text-indent: -0.25in;\">Dwarven Stoutness: When you are subject to forced movement, you may halve the number of squares you are forced to move, to a minimum of 1 square.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in; text-indent: -0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Resilient Metabolism: You gain a +5 racial bonus to recovery rolls against poison effects and a +2 bonus to Endurance checks to recover from disease or poison.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in; text-indent: -0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Stout Stamina: You may ignore speed penalties that result from wearing heavy armor, and any encumbrance penalties that result from wearing heavy armor are reduced to at most -2.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in; text-indent: -0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.3333px; text-indent: 0px;\">Traditionist Dwarf Weapon Proficiencies: Hammers and Picks</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in; text-indent: -0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Power: Dwarven Dedication: You have the <em>Dwarven Dedication</em>&nbsp;racial feature power, allowing you to regain vigor and ignore further harm.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Physical Qualities</span></u></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Dwarves average just 5 feet tall, but are very stocky, weighing as much as humans despite their height. Dwarves have the same variety of hair and skin colors as humans, although red and blonde hair is somewhat more common among them. They tend not to cut their hair, which is very thick and voluminous, instead working it into complex braids as a symbol of age and wisdom&mdash;the longer a dwarf&rsquo;s braids, the longer they have lived and the greater the respect they are given. Male dwarves can grow enormously bushy beards, but many choose to shave or keep it trimmed, especially if they work with complex machinery that might snag on facial hair.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Although dwarf children mature at the same rate as humans, dwarves are slow to feel the effects of old age, remaining hale and hearty well into their second century. Many live to be over 200 years old.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Culture and Attitudes</span></u></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Dwarven culture is split into two opposing factions, traditionist and modernist. The traditionists hold on desperately to the remnants of their culture from before the Collapse. They venerate their ancestors, and carefully preserve their knowledge and creations, causing them to be distrustful of technological progress. In addition to the pantheon worshipped by other races, the dwarves follow a form of ancestor worship overseen by a group of historian-priests called the Stonekeepers. The Stonekeepers keep records of a dwarf&rsquo;s accomplishments and deeds, and when a dwarf dies, his clan&rsquo;s Stonekeeper will evaluate what he did with his life to determine if he deserves to become one of the honored dead, immortalized in stone.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">While the dwarves were once the undisputed masters of stonecraft and metalworking, human industry has begun to compete with them. While dwarf artisans are still immensely skilled, the techniques developed by the ancient dwarves remain mostly unimproved-upon, while humans have developed new industrial methods. A person seeking an heirloom-quality weapon that his grandchildren will be proud to use would still do well to seek out a dwarf smith&mdash;but to equip an entire army, people now depend on human foundries, who can produce decent-quality goods quickly and cheaply.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Modernist dwarves have broken with the ancient ways of doing things and started adopting human inventions and improving them with dwarven skill and craftsmanship. Notably, the reloading mechanisms used in military-grade crossbows and firearms were developed by dwarves working for human arms manufacturers. The modernists remain a minority among dwarves, largely due to the Stonefathers&rsquo; condemnation. Many modernists are apprentice artisans, barely past their fourth decade, who have found themselves out of work as business increasingly goes to the humans instead of the master-smiths they work for. As a result, there is a growing expatriate dwarven presence in human cities, where they can find gainful employment&mdash;since even a dwarf apprentice is the equivalent of a skilled laborer among humans.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Both dwarven cultures place heavy emphasis on family relationships and form tight-knit extended family groups known as clans. Most dwarven businesses are owned by clans, rather than individuals, and most clans specialize in a handful of trades, training their children to follow in the family business. Young dwarves with talents that don&rsquo;t line up with their clan are often traded or sold to more fitting clans, although these days, the money is usually given to the young dwarf in question as a parting gift.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Dwarves in general appreciate a good day&rsquo;s work, followed by a stiff drink. They form close friendships, especially when they&rsquo;ve been separated from their clan for a while, and are fiercely loyal.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>"},"flags":[],"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
